      "updated_at": "2016-05-23 16:51:53 UTC",
      "body": "@jvican That output is intentional. If the class definition doesn't fit on a single line it will always break before extends. This is how the Scala.js style works and I thought would be nice to have in the default style as well.\r\n\r\nIt would be possible to add an option to get your second suggested output, but I would need convincing that it's worth the extra config flag. You can already get output that's similar to your first suggestion by opting into config style, just insert a newline after opening and before closing parenthesis."
    }
